pageContext.claim: “But when you're under audit, who would [give up tax returns]-- who would want to give them? It's a very big thing, but it would also take time, it would take -- and this -- people are going to get -- ultimately, people are going to be getting returns. They're going to see that.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump often makes turning over his tax returns seem impossible. It is not. President Richard Nixon released his tax returns while under audit.
